      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TRY CATCHING ME (5) had a tough draw and raced three wide last start so prepared to forgive that result. Had been racing very well prior with a string of top-four finishes, leading and fighting on well to miss by a head as runner-up here two back. Worth another chance. TRUTHBETOLD (4) was solid enough when beaten 7m from this barrier here last week and did put together a string of placings earlier in the campaign. Finds a suitable assignment so she is capable of playing a significant role. A LITTLE DILEMMA (7) hasn't been far from the placings in her last two appearance at Newcastle. Has had a month off but draws for a trail and could be dangerous. HAPPY TULHURST (9) has claims off a win from a similar draw two back at Dubbo.",
